# Next.js 15 Frontend — Production Cursor Rules

You are an expert in TypeScript, Node.js, React 19, Next.js 15 App Router, Aceternity UI, Radix Primitives, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion, Zod, and TanStack Query.

---

## 1. Project Architecture

Frontend and shared code live under `src/`. Backend-only code lives under `src/server/` (see [nextjs-api-backend-rules.mdc](.cursor/rules/nextjs-api-backend-rules.mdc)).

```
src/
├── app/                          # Next.js App Router (pages, layouts, api routes)
│   ├── (auth)/                   # Route groups
│   ├── (dashboard)/
│   ├── api/                      # API Route Handlers — import from @/server/...
│   ├── error.tsx                 # Segment-level error boundary
│   ├── global-error.tsx          # Root-level error boundary
│   ├── not-found.tsx
│   ├── layout.tsx
│   └── globals.css
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                       # Aceternity UI + Radix primitives + shadcn
│   │   ├── aceternity/
│   │   ├── primitives/
│   │   └── shadcn/
│   ├── common/                   # Shared composite components
│   └── features/                 # Feature-specific components, hooks, types co-located
│       └── competitor-radar/     # e.g. CompetitorCard.tsx, ScanProgress.tsx, index.ts
├── hooks/                        # Shared custom React hooks
├── lib/                          # Shared only — no server-only code here
│   ├── utils.ts                  # cn(), formatters, shared helpers
│   └── validations/              # Shared Zod schemas (forms, API validation types)
├── actions/                      # Next.js Server Actions — call @/server/services/...
│   └── users.actions.ts
├── stores/                       # Zustand (client-only state; not server data cache)
│   └── auth.store.ts
├── types/                        # Global TypeScript interfaces and types
├── constants/                    # App-wide constants and const maps
├── config/
│   └── env.ts                    # Zod-validated environment variables (shared)
├── middleware.ts                 # Route protection, auth checks
└── server/                       # Backend-only — see nextjs-api-backend-rules
```

- ALWAYS follow this directory structure.
- NEVER put business logic in page, layout, or component files. Call `@/server/services/...` from Server Actions or RSCs.
- NEVER import from `src/server/` in client components (no `'use client'` file may import server code).
- ALWAYS co-locate feature-specific components, hooks, and types inside `components/features/<feature-name>/`.
- NEVER create REST API routes when a Server Action is sufficient.
- Use lowercase with dashes for all directories (e.g., `components/auth-wizard`).

