## 2. TypeScript

- ALWAYS enable strict TypeScript: `"strict": true`, `"noUncheckedIndexedAccess": true`.
- NEVER use `any`. Use `unknown` with type guards, or define explicit interfaces.
- ALWAYS prefer `interface` over `type` for object shapes and component props.
- Use `type` only for unions, intersections, and aliases.
- NEVER use enums. Use `const` maps instead.
- ALWAYS export types/interfaces from a `types.ts` barrel file per feature.
- NEVER use `// @ts-ignore`. Use `// @ts-expect-error` with an explanatory comment.
- ALWAYS use the `satisfies` operator for config objects to preserve narrow types.
- Do NOT use default exports anywhere. ALWAYS use named exports.

```typescript
// ✅ Good
export interface UserCardProps {
  user: User;
  onSelect: (id: string) => void;
  isLoading?: boolean;
}

// ✅ Good — const map instead of enum
export const UserRole = {
  ADMIN: "admin",
  MEMBER: "member",
  GUEST: "guest",
} as const;
export type UserRole = (typeof UserRole)[keyof typeof UserRole];

// ❌ Bad
enum UserRole {
  ADMIN,
  MEMBER,
}
const UserCard = ({ user }: { user: any }) => {};
```

---

## 3. Component Standards

- ALWAYS use the `function` keyword for components. NEVER use `const` arrow functions for components.
- ALWAYS use named exports. NEVER use default exports.
- ALWAYS destructure props at the function signature level.
- ALWAYS place static content and interfaces at the bottom of the file.
- Use content variables for static content defined outside render functions.
- NEVER use class components. Use functional components only.
- Limit each file to one primary exported component. Sub-components may live in the same file only if they are never reused elsewhere.
- Use `React.memo` for pure components that receive stable, frequently-changing props.
- ALWAYS set `displayName` on components using `forwardRef` or HOCs.
- ALWAYS use declarative JSX. No imperative DOM manipulation.

```typescript
// ✅ Good
export function UserCard({ user, onSelect, isLoading = false }: UserCardProps) {
  if (isLoading) return <UserCardSkeleton />

  return (
    <div className={cn('rounded-lg p-4', !user.isActive && 'opacity-50')}>
      <p>{user.name}</p>
    </div>
  )
}

// Static content and interfaces at the bottom
const CARD_ARIA_LABEL = 'User profile card'

interface UserCardProps {
  user: User
  onSelect: (id: string) => void
  isLoading?: boolean
}
```

---

## 4. File & Naming Conventions

- Component files: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g., `UserCard.tsx`)
- Hook files: `camelCase.ts` prefixed with `use` (e.g., `useUserProfile.ts`)
- Server Action files: `camelCase.actions.ts` (e.g., `users.actions.ts`)
- Service files: `camelCase.service.ts` (e.g., `users.service.ts`)
- Store files: `camelCase.store.ts` (e.g., `auth.store.ts`)
- Utility files: `camelCase.ts` (e.g., `formatDate.ts`)
- Type files: `camelCase.types.ts` or `types.ts`
- Test files: `*.test.ts` / `*.spec.ts` co-located with source files
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` for values
- All directories: `lowercase-with-dashes`

