## 7. React Server Components (RSC) — Default

- DEFAULT to React Server Components. Only add `'use client'` when truly necessary.
- Use `'use client'` ONLY for:
  - Browser-only APIs (`window`, `navigator`, `localStorage`)
  - Interactive UI requiring local state or event handlers
  - Components using Framer Motion (`motion.*`) or Aceternity UI animations
  - Components using `useEffect`, `useState`, `useReducer`
- NEVER use `'use client'` for data fetching or global state management.
- NEVER use TanStack Query for data that can be fetched in a Server Component.
- Use `<Suspense>` boundaries with meaningful skeleton fallbacks for async RSCs.
- PREFER section-level `<Suspense>` (wrapping only the data-backed content) over broad `loading.tsx` route loaders. Keep static headers, titles, and descriptions **outside** `Suspense` so they always prerender immediately.
- Use `loading.tsx` only when an entire route segment must block until all content is ready.
- Prefer streaming and Server Components over client-side loading spinners; use shimmer/skeleton UIs instead of generic spinners.

```typescript
// ✅ Good — Server Component fetches data directly
export async function UserProfilePage({ params }: { params: { id: string } }) {
  const user = await userService.getById(params.id)
  return <UserProfile user={user} />
}

// ✅ Good — dashboard page with static header + Suspense-wrapped body using a shimmer
import { Suspense } from 'react'
import { DashboardShimmer } from '@/components/common'
import { StatusView } from '@/components/features/status/StatusView'
import { getStatusSummaryAction } from '@/actions/status.actions'

async function StatusContent() {
  const result = await getStatusSummaryAction()
  const agents = result.success && result.data ? result.data.agents : []
  const recentRuns = result.success && result.data ? result.data.recentRuns : []

  return <StatusView agents={agents} recentRuns={recentRuns} />
}

export default function StatusPage() {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen px-6 py-8 md:px-8 md:py-10">
      <header className="mb-10">
        {/* Static header always prerenders */}
      </header>
      <Suspense fallback={<DashboardShimmer />}>
        <StatusContent />
      </Suspense>
    </div>
  )
}
```

