## 16. Accessibility (a11y)

- ALWAYS use semantic HTML (`nav`, `main`, `article`, `section`, `header`, `footer`).
- ALWAYS add `aria-label`, `aria-describedby`, or `aria-live` where semantic HTML is insufficient.
- ALWAYS ensure all interactive elements are keyboard-navigable with visible focus rings.
- NEVER remove the default focus outline without providing a visible custom alternative.
- ALWAYS use Radix Primitives for complex interactive components — they handle a11y by default.
- ALWAYS respect `prefers-reduced-motion` for Aceternity/Framer Motion animations using `useReducedMotion()`.
- ALWAYS test with axe-core in CI.

```typescript
// ✅ Good — respect reduced motion in Aceternity components
'use client'
import { useReducedMotion } from 'framer-motion'

export function HeroSection() {
  const shouldReduceMotion = useReducedMotion()

  return (
    <section>
      {!shouldReduceMotion && <BackgroundBeams />}
      <h1>Welcome</h1>
    </section>
  )
}
```

