## 17. Code Quality & Patterns

- ALWAYS use the **Receive an Object, Return an Object (RORO)** pattern for functions with multiple parameters.
- ALWAYS use guard clauses. Handle errors and edge cases at the top of functions.
- NEVER use `else` after an early `return`. Use the if-return pattern.
- For single-line conditionals, omit curly braces: `if (condition) doSomething()`
- NEVER write deeply nested `if` statements. Flatten with early returns.
- Omit semicolons (configure Prettier accordingly).
- ALWAYS write JSDoc comments for exported utility functions and service methods.
- ALWAYS add a barrel `index.ts` for each major directory.
- NEVER commit commented-out code. Use feature flags instead.
- Max file length: 300 lines. Refactor if exceeded.
- Max function length: 50 lines. Extract helpers if exceeded.
- ALWAYS run ESLint with `eslint-config-next` and stricter custom rules.
- ALWAYS use Prettier for formatting. No manual formatting.
- ALWAYS use Husky + lint-staged for pre-commit hooks.

