## 18. Testing

- ALWAYS write unit tests for utilities, hooks, and services.
- ALWAYS write integration tests for critical user flows using `@testing-library/react`.
- Use `vitest` for unit tests and `@testing-library/react` for component tests.
- ALWAYS mock external API calls and Server Actions in tests. NEVER hit real endpoints.
- ALWAYS mock Framer Motion in tests to avoid animation-related test flakiness:
  ```typescript
  vi.mock("framer-motion", () => ({
    motion: { div: "div", span: "span" },
    AnimatePresence: ({ children }) => children,
  }));
  ```
- Aim for >80% coverage on business-critical services and utilities.
- Test file structure mirrors source file structure.

