## 19. Observability

- ALWAYS integrate Sentry for error tracking.
- ALWAYS call `captureException` inside `error.tsx` and `global-error.tsx`.
- ALWAYS log meaningful context (userId, route, action name) alongside errors.
- NEVER log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, PII).
- ALWAYS monitor Core Web Vitals — pay special attention to CLS and INP when using Aceternity animations.

---

## 20. Commit & PR Standards

- Use Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`, `test:`.
- NEVER commit directly to `main`. Always use feature branches + PR reviews.
- PR titles must follow Conventional Commits format.
- ALWAYS run ESLint, Prettier, and `tsc --noEmit` in CI before merge.
- ALWAYS link every PR to an issue or ticket.
